The paper deals with strategy improvement algorithms for concurrent games played on graphs, which is a topic that falls under game theory (cs.GT). The algorithm presented in the paper involves computing the maximal probability with which player 1 can enforce the safety objective, which requires techniques from logic and automata theory (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the use of value-iteration algorithms, which are commonly used in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithm involves manipulating graphs and computing probabilities, which are topics that fall under data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with the convergence of upper and lower bounds, which is a topic that falls under programming languages (cs.PL).
